Weekly Randomizing Groups - ZOO/BIO 102

Tiago Ribeiro

January 10, 2018

On Fall 2017, I chose to weekly randomize the groups on one of my ZOO/BIO 102 sections, instead of using the approaching of assigning students to fixed groups on the third week of the class. To understand how the students perceived this group assignment approach, I gave them a survey at the end of the semester. Herein, I present the compiled results of the surveys applied to 21 students.
